d that it is planning to adopt the Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\'s (“BCBS”) guidance on credit risk and accounting for expected credit losses, which was published on 18 December 2015. The new BCBS guidance replaces an earlier document on sound credit risk assessments and valuation for loans, issued in 2006, and sets out supervisory expectations for banks on sound credit risk practices associated with implementing and applying an expected credit loss (“ECL”) accounting framework.</p>\n<p>	In a recent circular, the HKMA said the move to ECL accounting frameworks by accounting standard setters was an important step forward in addressing weaknesses related to credit loss recognition, which were identified during the financial crisis.</p>\n<p>	The regulator said it encouraged all authorised institutions to review their credit risk management processes in light of the relevant principles set out in the BCBS guidance.</p>\n<p>	The HKMA said the development of ECL accounting frameworks was consistent with the G20\'s aim for accounting standard setters to \"strengthen accounting recognition of loan loss provisions by incorporating a broader range of credit information\".<br />\n	 </p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:44:\"<p>Trond Vagen, Regulatory Intelligence</p>\n\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_image\";a:0:{}s:14:\"field_contents\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:3:\"661\";}}}s:20:\"field_practice_areas\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:3:\"576\";}}}s:12:\"field_images\";a:0:{}s:14:\"field_featured\";a:0:{}s:11:\"title_field\";a:1:{s:7:\"zh-hant\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"value\";s:44:\"HKMA to Follow Basel Guidance on Credit Risk\";s:6:\"format\";N;s:10:\"safe_value\";s:44:\"HKMA to Follow Basel Guidance on Credit Risk\";}}}s:13:\"field_authors\";a:0:{}s:19:\"field_journal_issue\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:5:\"value\";s:19:\"2014-12-01 08:00:00\";s:8:\"timezone\";s:14:\"Asia/Hong_Kong\";s:11:\"timezone_db\";s:14:\"Asia/Hong_K