ng_Kong\";s:9:\"date_type\";s:8:\"datetime\";}}}s:19:\"field_jurisdictions\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_video\";a:0:{}s:14:\"title_original\";s:52:\"香港海事法律獎學金2015/16證書頒獎典禮\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:11:{s:11:\"field_image\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:2:{i:0;s:8:\"og:image\";i:1;s:12:\"rdfs:seeAlso\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:10:\"dc:subject\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:7:\"rdftype\";a:2:{i:0;s:9:\"sioc:Item\";i:1;s:13:\"foaf:Document\";}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:8:\"dc:title\";}}s:7:\"created\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"dc:date\";i:1;s:10:\"dc:created\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}s:7:\"changed\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:11:\"dc:modified\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:15:\"content:encoded\";}}s:3:\"uid\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:16:\"sioc:has_creator\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:4:\"name\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:9:\"foaf:name\";}}s:13:\"comment_count\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:16:\"sioc:num_replies\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:11:\"xsd:integer\";}s:13:\"last_activity\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:23:\"sioc:last_activity_date\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}}s:3:\"cid\";s:1:\"0\";s:22:\"last_comment_timestamp\";s:10:\"1454929181\";s:17:\"last_comment_name\";N;s:16:\"last_comment_uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"name\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"picture\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"data\";s:241:\"a:7:{s:5:\"block\";a:1:{s:6:\"system\";a:1:{s:4:\"main\";i:0;}}s:16:\"ckeditor_default\";s:1:\"t\";s:20:\"ckeditor_show_toggle\";s:1:\"t\";s:14:\"ckeditor_width\";s:4:\"100%\";s:13:\"ckeditor_lang\";s:2:\"en\";s:18:\"ckeditor_auto_lang\";s:1:\"t\";s:7:\"overlay\";i:1;}\";}',0,1458184477,1),('9265','O:8:\"stdClass\":39:{s:3:\"vid\";s:4:\"9269\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Gourmet Trip to Barcelona 2015\";s:3:\"log\";s:29:\"Created by FeedsNodeProcessor\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"comment\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"promote\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"sticky\";s:1:\"1\";s:3:\"nid\";s:4:\"9265\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"article\";s:8:\"language\";s:2:\"en\";s:7:\"created\";s:10:\"1454284800\";s:7:\"changed\";s:10:\"1455077877\";s:4:\"tnid\";s:4:\"9265\";s:9:\"translate\";s:1:\"0\";s:18:\"revision_timestamp\";s:10:\"1455077877\";s:12:\"revision_uid\";s:3:\"217\";s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:3215:\"\r\n\r\n<p>In July 2015, the Law Society Cookery, Food and Wine Appreciation Group took a fascinating gourmet trip to Barcelona, a city of sunshine and sea breeze.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Welcome Dinner</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our amazing tour began with a private-kitchen dinner, hosted by two top Spanish chefs. As soon as we arrived at their house, we were ushered to their chic garden where we were greeted with cocktails. We then moved to their dining room, next to their open kitchen, where we enjoyed an eight-course modern Spanish dinner with a South American touch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The chefs wow-ed us as they prepared a variety of inventive dishes before our eyes – Jerusalem artichoke purée with orange reduction, an egg with truffle cooked at 64°C and a wonderful turbot with sweet chestnuts and mushrooms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After dinner, we transformed the dining room into a live music hall. A member showcased her piano skills by playing several all-time classics, which eventually evolved into a Spanish Cantata with the chefs and staff!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Cooking Classes</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To deepen our understanding of Spanish cuisine during our stay, we also attended a three-day cooking class, where we learned about Traditional Spanish Cooking, Molecular Cooking and Dessert Making under the guidance of Chef Fatima Gismero and Chef Alfonso Tomassoni. At the end of the course, we were all awarded certificates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Michelin Night</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The highlight of this trip was our dinner at an impeccable contemporary-style restaurant that has earned two Michelin stars since it was founded in January 2006. It is led by Chef Martin Berasategui, who holds more Michelin stars than any other Spanish chef (ie, 7 stars). The aromas and flavours of every dish were an infusion of his gastronomic vision on Basque cuisine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The eight-course tasting menu was tailor-made for us. One of the more interesting plates we received soon after being seated was one containing five different kinds of butter (beetroot, mushroom, spinach, tomato and regular butter) that spanned the colours of the rainbow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even with all of the inventive cuisine we tried, this fantastic dinner would not have been the same without cava! With glasses of the bubbling drink on the house, we certainly enjoyed the warm hospitality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Flamenco Class</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We thought our trip would be incomplete without Spanish Flamenco dancing, so we attended an hour-long beginner’s class at the beachfront Civic Centre of Barceloneta. Even though we may not have perfected the dance itself, our effort sure counts!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those who are interested to know more about our Gourmet Trip. Please contact group convenor, Mr. Nick Chan (<a href=\"mailto:Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com\">Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com</a>).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Looking forward</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Members of the Cookery, Food and Wine Appreciation Group have already commenced with planning of our 2016 trip to Vietnam. Please contact Mr. Nick Chan, if you would like to learn more or join us!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>David Ting<br />\r\nMember of Cookery, Food &amp; Wine Appreciation Group</em></p>\r\n\";s:7:\"summary\";s:25:\"<p>Law Society News</p>\r\n\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:3161:\"<p>In July 2015, the Law Society Cookery, Food and Wine Appreciation Group took a fascinating gourmet trip to Barcelona, a city of sunshine and sea breeze.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Welcome Dinner</strong></em></p>\n<p>Our amazing tour began with a private-kitchen dinner, hosted by two top Spanish chefs. As soon as we arrived at their house, we were ushered to their chic garden where we were greeted with cocktails. We then moved to their dining room, next to their open kitchen, where we enjoyed an eight-course modern Spanish dinner with a South American touch.</p>\n<p>The chefs wow-ed us as they prepared a variety of inventive dishes before our eyes – Jerusalem artichoke purée with orange reduction, an egg with truffle cooked at 64°C and a wonderful turbot with sweet chestnuts and mushrooms.</p>\n<p>After dinner, we transformed the dining room into a live music hall. A member showcased her piano skills by playing several all-time classics, which eventually evolved into a Spanish Cantata with the chefs and staff!</p>\n<p><em><strong>Cooking Classes</strong></em></p>\n<p>To deepen our understanding of Spanish cuisine during our stay, we also attended a three-day cooking class, where we learned about Traditional Spanish Cooking, Molecular Cooking and Dessert Making under the guidance of Chef Fatima Gismero and Chef Alfonso Tomassoni. At the end of the course, we were all awarded certificates.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Michelin Night</strong></em></p>\n<p>The highlight of this trip was our dinner at an impeccable contemporary-style restaurant that has earned two Michelin stars since it was founded in January 2006. It is led by Chef Martin Berasategui, who holds more Michelin stars than any other Spanish chef (ie, 7 stars). The aromas and flavours of every dish were an infusion of his gastronomic vision on Basque cuisine.</p>\n<p>The eight-course tasting menu was tailor-made for us. One of the more interesting plates we received soon after being seated was one containing five different kinds of butter (beetroot, mushroom, spinach, tomato and regular butter) that spanned the colours of the rainbow.</p>\n<p>Even with all of the inventive cuisine we tried, this fantastic dinner would not have been the same without cava! With glasses of the bubbling drink on the house, we certainly enjoyed the warm hospitality.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Flamenco Class</strong></em></p>\n<p>We thought our trip would be incomplete without Spanish Flamenco dancing, so we attended an hour-long beginner’s class at the beachfront Civic Centre of Barceloneta. Even though we may not have perfected the dance itself, our effort sure counts!</p>\n<p>For those who are interested to know more about our Gourmet Trip. Please contact group convenor, Mr. Nick Chan (<a href=\"mailto:Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com\">Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com</a>).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Looking forward</strong></em></p>\n<p>Members of the Cookery, Food and Wine Appreciation Group have already commenced with planning of our 2016 trip to Vietnam. Please contact Mr. Nick Chan, if you would like to learn more or join us!</p>\n<p><em>David Ting<br />\nMember of Cookery, Food &amp; Wine Appreciation Group</em></p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:24:\"<p>Law Society News</p>\n\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_image\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:17:{s:3:\"fid\";s:3:\"423\";s:3:\"uid\";s:3:\"217\";s:8:\"filename\";s:11:\"lsn_17.jpeg\";s:3:\"uri\";s:32:\"public://field/image/lsn_17.jpeg\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"209104\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1455077746\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";s:25:\"field_file_image_alt_text\";a:0:{}s:27:\"field_file_image_title_text\";a:0:{}s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}s:8:\"metadata\";a:2:{s:6:\"height\";i:630;s:5:\"width\";i:945;}s:3:\"alt\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"height\";s:3:\"630\";s:5:\"width\";s:3:\"945\";}}}s:14:\"field_contents\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:3:\"484\";}}}s:20:\"field_practice_areas\";a:0:{}s:12:\"field_images\";a:0:{}s:14:\"field_featured\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:5:\"value\";s:14:\"FeaturedBlock1\";}}}s:11:\"title_field\";a:1:{s:2:\"en\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"value\";s:30:\"Gourmet Trip to Barcelona 2015\";s:6:\"format\";N;s:10:\"safe_value\";s:30:\"Gourmet Trip to Barcelona 2015\";}}}s:13:\"field_authors\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:3:\"611\";}}}s:19:\"field_journal_issue\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:5:\"value\";s:19:\"2016-02-01 00:00:00\";s:8:\"timezone\";s:14:\"Asia/Hong_Kong\";s:11:\"timezone_db\";s:14:\"Asia/Hong_Kong\";s:9:\"date_type\";s:8:\"datetime\";}}}s:19:\"field_jurisdictions\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_video\";a:0:{}s:14:\"title_original\";s:30:\"Gourmet Trip to Barcelona 2015\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:11:{s:11:\"field_image\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:2:{i:0;s:8:\"og:image\";i:1;s:12:\"rdfs:seeAlso\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:10:\"dc:subject\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:7:\"rdftype\";a:2:{i:0;s:9:\"sioc:Item\";i:1;s:13:\"foaf:Document\";}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:8:\"dc:title\";}}s:7:\"created\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"dc:date\";i:1;s:10:\"dc:created\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}s:7:\"changed\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:11:\"dc:modified\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:15:\"content:encoded\";}}s:3:\"uid\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:16:\"sioc:has_creator\";}s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"rel\";}s:4:\"name\";a:1:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:9:\"foaf:name\";}}s:13:\"comment_count\";a:2:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:16:\"sioc:num_replies\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:11:\"xsd:integer\";}s:13:\"last_activity\";a:3:{s:10:\"predicates\";a:1:{i:0;s:23:\"sioc:last_activity_date\";}s:8:\"datatype\";s:12:\"xsd:dateTime\";s:8:\"callback\";s:12:\"date_iso8601\";}}s:3:\"cid\";s:1:\"0\";s:22:\"last_comment_timestamp\";s:10:\"1454929181\";s:17:\"last_comment_name\";N;s:16:\"last_comment_uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"name\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"picture\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"data\";s:241:\"a:7:{s:5:\"block\";a:1:{s:6:\"system\";a:1:{s:4:\"main\";i:0;}}s:16:\"ckeditor_default\";s:1:\"t\";s:20:\"ckeditor_show_toggle\";s:1:\"t\";s:14:\"ckeditor_width\";s:4:\"100%\";s:13:\"ckeditor_lang\";s:2:\"en\";s:18:\"ckeditor_auto_lang\";s:1:\"t\";s:7:\"overlay\";i:1;}\";}',0,1458112328,1),('9266','O:8:\"stdClass\":39:{s:3:\"vid\";s:4:\"9270\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"2015年巴塞隆拿美食之旅\";s:3:\"log\";s:29:\"Created by FeedsNodeProcessor\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"comment\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"promote\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"sticky\";s:1:\"1\";s:3:\"nid\";s:4:\"9266\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"article\";s:8:\"language\";s:7:\"zh-hant\";s:7:\"created\";s:10:\"1454284800\";s:7:\"changed\";s:10:\"1455077858\";s:4:\"tnid\";s:4:\"9265\";s:9:\"translate\";s:1:\"0\";s:18:\"revision_timestamp\";s:10:\"1455077858\";s:12:\"revision_uid\";s:3:\"217\";s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:2594:\"\r\n\r\n<p>2015年7月，律師會烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組前往陽光與海灘城市巴塞隆拿，歡度了一個美食之旅。</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>歡迎晚宴</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>美妙的旅程由兩位頂級西班牙廚師主理的私房菜晚宴展開序幕。甫到達他們家，我們便被引領到別緻的花園，享用雞尾酒。然後，我們轉移到飯廳，在開放式廚房旁邊享用帶南美特色的八道菜現代西班牙晚餐。</p>\r\n\r\n<p>廚師在我們眼前炮製一道道新穎的菜色，令我們讚嘆不已，包括香橙汁菊芋泥、低溫煮蛋配松露及多寶魚配甜栗子和香菇。</p>\r\n\r\n<p>晚飯後，飯廳變成了現場音樂廳。一位會員大顯鋼琴技藝，彈奏多首經典名曲，最後廚師和工作人員也加入，組成西班牙大合唱！</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>烹飪班</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>為加深對西班牙菜的了解，旅程中我們也參加了為期三天的烹飪班，跟隨名廚Fatima Gismero及Alfonso Tomassoni學習傳統西班牙烹飪、分子料理和甜點製作。課程完成後，眾人均獲頒發證書。</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>米芝蓮之夜</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>此行的亮點是在一間米芝蓮餐廳享用的晚餐。這家現代風格的米芝蓮2星級餐廳於2006年1月開業，由米芝蓮7星名廚Martin Berasategui主理，摘星量冠絕西班牙。晚餐中的每道菜均色香味俱全，展示他對巴斯克菜的味覺視野。</p>\r\n\r\n<p>這八道菜晚餐是為我們度身訂造的。其中一道有趣的菜式加入了5種不同口味的牛油(紅菜頭、香菇、菠菜、番茄和普通牛油)，組成彩虹的色彩。</p>\r\n\r\n<p>佳餚配美酒，嚐盡各款創意美食後，這頓美妙晚餐當然不可缺少cava氣泡酒！一杯杯「西班牙香檳」下肚，我們盡享餐廳的熱情款待。</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>佛蘭明高舞蹈班</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>西班牙之旅若缺少了佛蘭明高舞蹈總覺得美中不足，因此我們參加了巴塞隆拿海濱文娛中心的一小時舞蹈初班。雖然我們的舞技可能未盡完美，但卻努力可嘉！</p>\r\n\r\n<p>想了解巴塞隆拿美食之旅的詳情，請聯絡小組召集人陳曉峰律師(<a href=\"mailto:Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com\">Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com</a>)。</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>展望未來</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組成員已開始計劃2016年的越南之旅。如欲了解更多或報名參加，請聯絡陳曉峰律師。</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>丁志浩律師<br />\r\n烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組成員</em></p>\r\n\";s:7:\"summary\";s:24:\"<p>律師會新聞</p>\r\n\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:2540:\"<p>2015年7月，律師會烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組前往陽光與海灘城市巴塞隆拿，歡度了一個美食之旅。</p>\n<p><em><strong>歡迎晚宴</strong></em></p>\n<p>美妙的旅程由兩位頂級西班牙廚師主理的私房菜晚宴展開序幕。甫到達他們家，我們便被引領到別緻的花園，享用雞尾酒。然後，我們轉移到飯廳，在開放式廚房旁邊享用帶南美特色的八道菜現代西班牙晚餐。</p>\n<p>廚師在我們眼前炮製一道道新穎的菜色，令我們讚嘆不已，包括香橙汁菊芋泥、低溫煮蛋配松露及多寶魚配甜栗子和香菇。</p>\n<p>晚飯後，飯廳變成了現場音樂廳。一位會員大顯鋼琴技藝，彈奏多首經典名曲，最後廚師和工作人員也加入，組成西班牙大合唱！</p>\n<p><em><strong>烹飪班</strong></em></p>\n<p>為加深對西班牙菜的了解，旅程中我們也參加了為期三天的烹飪班，跟隨名廚Fatima Gismero及Alfonso Tomassoni學習傳統西班牙烹飪、分子料理和甜點製作。課程完成後，眾人均獲頒發證書。</p>\n<p><em><strong>米芝蓮之夜</strong></em></p>\n<p>此行的亮點是在一間米芝蓮餐廳享用的晚餐。這家現代風格的米芝蓮2星級餐廳於2006年1月開業，由米芝蓮7星名廚Martin Berasategui主理，摘星量冠絕西班牙。晚餐中的每道菜均色香味俱全，展示他對巴斯克菜的味覺視野。</p>\n<p>這八道菜晚餐是為我們度身訂造的。其中一道有趣的菜式加入了5種不同口味的牛油(紅菜頭、香菇、菠菜、番茄和普通牛油)，組成彩虹的色彩。</p>\n<p>佳餚配美酒，嚐盡各款創意美食後，這頓美妙晚餐當然不可缺少cava氣泡酒！一杯杯「西班牙香檳」下肚，我們盡享餐廳的熱情款待。</p>\n<p><em><strong>佛蘭明高舞蹈班</strong></em></p>\n<p>西班牙之旅若缺少了佛蘭明高舞蹈總覺得美中不足，因此我們參加了巴塞隆拿海濱文娛中心的一小時舞蹈初班。雖然我們的舞技可能未盡完美，但卻努力可嘉！</p>\n<p>想了解巴塞隆拿美食之旅的詳情，請聯絡小組召集人陳曉峰律師(<a href=\"mailto:Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com\">Nick.Chan@SquirePB.com</a>)。</p>\n<p><em><strong>展望未來</strong></em></p>\n<p>烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組成員已開始計劃2016年的越南之旅。如欲了解更多或報名參加，請聯絡陳曉峰律師。</p>\n<p><em>丁志浩律師<br />\n烹飪、美酒佳餚鑑賞小組成員</em></p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:23:\"<p>律師會新聞</p>\n\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_image\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:17:{s:3:\"fid\";s:3:\"424\";s:3:\"uid\";s:3:\"217\";s:8:\"filename\";s:11:\"lsn_17.jpeg\";s:3:\"uri\";s:34:\"public://field/image/lsn_17_0.jpeg\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"2