 officers from Heilongjiang led by Mr.Zou Dali of the Judiciary Department of Heilongjiang Provincial, visited the Law Society on 9 December 2015 and were received by Greater China Legal Affairs Committee member and former President Anthony Chow, Mr.Franki Cheung, Ms.Catherine Mun and Secretary-General Heidi Chu. The Law Society exchanged views on professional development and management in the legal industry with the delegates, who were particularly interested in the Law Society’s role in law firm risk management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/uploads/images/Issues/Feb2016/LSN_10.jpeg\" width=\"537\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Representatives of the Law Society with the delegation of appointed attesting officers from Heilongjiang.</p>\r\n\";s:7:\"summary\";s:25:\"<p>Law Society News</p>\r\n\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:776:\"<p>A delegation of 10 appointed attesting officers from Heilongjiang led by Mr.Zou Dali of the Judiciary Department of Heilongjiang Provincial, visited the Law Society on 9 December 2015 and were received by Greater China Legal Affairs Committee member and former President Anthony Chow, Mr.Franki Cheung, Ms.Catherine Mun and Secretary-General Heidi Chu. The Law Society exchanged views on professional development and management in the legal industry with the delegates, who were particularly interested in the Law Society’s role in law firm risk management.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/uploads/images/Issues/Feb2016/LSN_10.jpeg\" width=\"537\" /></p>\n<p>Representatives of the Law Society with the delegation of appointed attesting officers from Heilongjiang.</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:24:\"<p>Law Society News</p>\n\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:11:\"field_image\";a:0:{}s:14:\"field_contents\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:3:\"484\";}}}s:20:\"field_practice_areas\";a:0:{}s:12:\"field_images\";a:0:{}s:14:\"field_featured\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:5:\"value\";s:14:\"Fe